fr.beaftech.collique

Class SingleElementCollection<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.beaftech.collique.SingleElementCollection<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the element to store
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SingleElementList, SingleElementSet

    public abstract class SingleElementCollection<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Collection<E>
    Single element implementation of Collection interface. Permits all elements, including null and implements all optional collection operations except Collection.add(Object) which needs to be override by subclasses. Note that, by design addAll(Collection) is directly linked to Collection.add(Object) so its behavior (espescially for addition restriction) will depends of subclasses implementation.
    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Arnould Guidat
